@SECWAR “Many of you – even in your short time in uniform – have endured what I call the 'slow slide' of the U.S. Army. You’ve seen standards lowered.

You’ve seen the obsession with race and gender. You’ve seen the watering down of discipline, codes weakened, and traditions tossed aside in the name of political correctness. Statues taken down. Paintings placed in the basement.

I am here to tell you: The slow slide — here at West Point and across the United States Army — IS OVER."

